<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="339" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d339">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 862.20261/28</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul at Tiflis</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Smith</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 106</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-11-12">
                                        <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department acknowledges the
                                receipt of your despatch of October 4, 1917, No. 66,<note n="1" xml:id="d339fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_294">p.
                                    294</ref>.</note> on the subject of propaganda among the Kurdish
                                tribes. As the purpose of your suggestion appears to be the
                                organization of an uprising against the Turks, with whose Government
                                the United States is not at war, it is not possible for the
                                Department to approve the interesting plan which you suggest.</p>
                            <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>For the Secretary of State: <lb/>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>